{
  "stem": "6719.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It also, sometimes, was done for somebody to hide something somewhere, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So he took a cut of that if he knew that the guy was down there that really wanted to hide something.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now, the-- the-- the funny part-- and that, yes, that was mentioned at the party that they had in Israel-- was that there was a man, a German Jewish boy, that came from Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And his name was, uh, Heinrich Hartman-- Hartman, H-A-R-T-M-A-N.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He's dead now.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He died from a place in Haiti.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he had a lame leg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was his-- I don't know if it was the right leg or the left leg.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was stiff.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it was like that, straight up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And uh, whenever he went in there, because of the position, the only thing that were-- that was sticking out was his leg.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we always knew that Henry was in the can.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so sometimes we tried to walk by him and push the leg, and he used to swear like hell.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's amusing, OK?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This same Henry nearly became the husband of my-- of my wife instead of me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's a good thing she married me instead of him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because his-- you know, it's a small world-- his father left-- he was shot in Dunkirk, incidentally, Henry, at the evacuation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then he had to go back, and he was picked up in Belgium and sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and his father got across at the evacuation of Dunkirk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he met my mother-in-law, my wife's mother, and they got married, because her husband was killed in Auschwitz, too-- her true father, my wife's father.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
